    <section class="kicker">OPINION</section>

    <h1 class="headline">Your Headline Goes Here</h1>
    <p class="deck">A one–two sentence subtitle that frames the argument like a real editorial.</p>

    <div class="byline">
      <span class="author">By Ayan Khan</span>
      <span class="dot">•</span>
      <time datetime="2026-02-28">February 28, 2026</time>
    </div>

    <article class="story">
      <p class="lead"><span class="dropcap">T</span>his is your opening paragraph. Make it sharp. Make it human. Make it feel like it belongs in a paper.</p>

      <p>Second paragraph. Add context. What’s happening, what changed, and why should anyone care?</p>

      <blockquote class="pullquote">
        “Put a strong pull quote here — something that sounds inevitable.”
      </blockquote>

      <p>Keep writing your argument. Add a counterpoint. Then dismantle it calmly.</p>

      <h2>A clean section header</h2>
      <p>Finish with a closing paragraph that lands the point without overexplaining.</p>
    </article>

